race.comment: PRETTY SLICK (5) goes well for hoop Butler who has a win and three placings from just four steers and has been racing very consistently of late. Saves her best form for this track and trip and looks the one they all have to run down. FORTRESS AUSTRALIA (2) has only missed a drum once in six spins around this circuit and gets a stack of weight relief with the 3kg claim. Looms as the main danger. TORQUE I TEE (4) strips fitter second-up from the break and gets the services of Wiggins in the irons from the inside alley. Ticks a few boxes. YOUR TOO GOOD (1) will be high on confidence following that last-start victory and can make his presence felt. LADY TOWNSON (3) has a win and a placing from four starts at this venue and may run a race at odds.
